node.title: Police arrest member of far-right movement in Te Puke
node.description: Police have arrested a man involved in New Zealand's far-right movement in Te Puke.
node.content:
["Police have arrested a man involved in New Zealand's far-right movement in Te Puke.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Claire Eastham-Farrelly\n
", "Footage of the arrest shows plain-clothes officers with side-carry handguns walking the man to a patrol car in handcuffs.", "A police spokesperson says officers executed a search warrant at an address on Number 2 Road this morning.", "During the operation, a 39-year-old man refused to leave the premises and was arrested.", "He is due to appear in the Tauranga District court on 4 April.", "He has been charged with obstructing police, but police say other charges are under consideration."]
